&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diversity at Altos&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Altos Labs has been named one of the Top 3 Biotech Companies and ranked for the second year on the Forbes 2026 Best Startups in America list. &amp;nbsp;At Altos, exceptional scientists and industry leaders from around the world work together to advance a shared mission. Our intentional focus is on Belonging, so that all employees know that they are valued for their unique perspectives. We are all accountable for sustaining a diverse and inclusive environment.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Contribute To Altos&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Altos, your work will be at the heart of a mission to transform medicine by reversing disease and restoring cell health. You will contribute to the development of a new generation of drugs rooted in an advanced understanding of cellular rejuvenation and resilience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Research Specialist or Sr Scientist of Assay Sciences, Discovery Pharmacology team, your primary focus will be supporting the needs of development and operation of a wide range of analytical and bioassays within the Drug Discovery and Development (3DS) division of Altos. This is a laboratory research scientist position focused on the development and execution of cell-based and biochemical assays, and complex in vitro bioassays. Your work will contribute to our drug discovery campaigns across a diverse portfolio of discovery and development stage projects. Your expertise will be instrumental in driving our mission and making a significant impact in aging/rejuvenation biology and drug discovery.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll be right in the middle of drug discovery, developing the next generation of medicines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your main gig is making, running, and optimizing a ton of analytical and bioassays (cell-based, biochemical, complex &lt;em&gt;in vitro&lt;/em&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll be taking manual assays and turning them into super-efficient, automated processes—think moving from a bench to high-throughput screening with automated gear.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll need to nail the stats (Z’-factor!) and make sure everything is scalable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating new assays from scratch (de novo development) is also on the list.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documenting &lt;em&gt;everything&lt;/em&gt; in the electronic lab notebook (ELN) for awesome data integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with other teams, including the Discovery Sciences, Institute of Computation and Product Development crew.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll be a technical lead for the assay sciences team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll also be managing external research partners (CROs) to make sure their data is top-notch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
